speech.p: The pro-Assad media organisation al-Watan yesterday reported, unequivocally, that Russian jets were involved in striking targets in Ghouta. Is it the Foreign Secretary’s understanding that in recent days Russian jets have struck targets and broken the ceasefire that the Secretary Council called for just on Saturday, in its resolution?

My hon. Friend has given two excellent examples. There are plans for a super-garrison at Catterick. I understand that service accommodation was meant to be completed by 2020 but is now estimated at 2023, which will clearly create cost overruns around the CarillionAmey contract. Again, we are seeing a lack of maintenance on that contract, which will end up costing us more. We are seeing cost overruns in not just equipment but a whole range of areas, including accommodation.
